description: Recently sold: $230,000. Welcome home! Don't miss out on your opportunity to live in this lovely home, located in the heart of a great school district. Conveniently located near schools, entertainment and shopping centers, all of your family needs will be fulfilled! It is the perfect affordable home for growing families or those looking to downsize, with an amazing yard for kids to play and family entertainment!

Recently sold: $345,000. Professional photos, 3D tour and aerials coming soon. Listing on MLS on Friday the 23rd of August. For pre-MLS questions and access please contact listing agents Lyman and Denise Jenkins at 612.490.2733 OR 612.418.6044 OR TeamJenkins@Results.net. 

You will love this move in ready Blaine rambler!! Enjoy one level living on a huge 1/2 acre corner lot with 3 bedrooms and 3 full baths. Enjoy morning Joe on your 4 season porch overlooking your huge back yard with walls of windows and abundant natural light throughout the home. The home boasts an enormous kitchen with hardwood floors, upgraded stainless appliances, tons of cabinet space, a breakfast bar and large bay window at the sink. There is a large 20x12 deck facing the back yard and a second smaller 8x6 deck for cooking off the dining room. The lot is surrounded by sidewalks and is fully landscaped with irrigation, plenty of trees, retaining walls and beautiful perennial gardens. 

The main level consists of the epitome of an open concept living space (kitchen/living room/dining room/4-season-porch); laundry with upgraded Samsung machines, cabinets and a sink; an owner's ensuite with a walk-in closet and a recently remodeled AWESOME full bath; and a large second bedroom with full bath across the hall. Both bedrooms on the main level have ceiling fans. Greet old man winter (remember him?) with your gas fireplace in the living room, and engage your desired privacy with custom Bali and Levolor honeycomb blinds. 

Journey with me to the fully finished walkout basement with a 22x20 family room one large bedroom and a full bath. There is approximately 400 square feet of unfinished additional storage with included shelving, cabinets and a workbench in the furnace room and adjacent storage room. 

UPDATES AND OTHER FEATURES INCLUDE:
New roof and siding 2018. Newer kitchen appliances, 5 burner gas range with two ovens (one convection), new fridge, dishwasher,water heater and water softener. High efficiency furnace. Air exchanger. Furnace humidifier. Simplisafe alarm system installed. MyQ garage door management. Fully insulated oversized two car garage. Newly remodeled master bath with granite, soaker tub, new shower and double vanity with soft close doors and drawers. TP Link wireless light switches on select lights controllable manually or through Kasa app. Works with Amazon echo. Honeywell wireless thermostat controllable manually or from anywhere with cellphone. LED lighting throughout the home with lots of dimmers. 

Neighborhood Description

Quiet and easy access to schools and Bunker Hills Regional Park, golf course and Bunker Beach.  This is a newer development in Blaine - construction began in 2005 and finished in 2013. Easy access to everything along HWY 65; Riverdale shopping district; HWY 10 and so much more.

Recently sold: $260,515. REMODELED IN 2005 WITH ONLY THE BEST inside & out with Andersen windows, Diamond cherry cabinets, Silestone, marble, Kohler bath, porcelain tile. Oak doors, floors, woodwork. Beautifully landscaped, private backyard, pond. Super clean & move-in ready.  For sale by owner.  For complete specs, enter MLS 4402427 at http://msp.themlsonline.com/.  Call Ron 763-228-8452 for appointment.



Neighborhood Description



We've lived in this neighborhood for 25 years, and in part, because you couldn't ask for a better location for convenient access to everything.  

Just two streets away is fast food like Subway, Burger King, Taco Bell; gas station, Walgreens, liquor store, and a new Chinese restaurant.  

Less than 5 minutes away is Super Target, new 24-hour Walmart, Menards, Lowes, Kohls, Cub Foods, Marshalls, Northtown Mall and many more restaurants, like Noodle Bowl, Red Lobster, Chili's, and Outback.  

We're far enough away from the freeway for the home to be quiet, but we're still centrally located and close to Hwy 10 for 35W, or 610 for 252, or Hwy 65. From this location you can get to downtown Minneapolis or shopping in Maple Grove in 20 minutes, Edina in 25 minutes, and the airport in 35 minutes.  

Express bus service at Foley Park & Ride is a few miles away with Route 852.  Express buses also pick up within a block of the home with Route 854.
